HEADWORD: Capercally
<hw>Ca"per*cal`ly</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael,
<ets>capulcoile</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A species of black
Old World grouse (<spn>Tetrao uragallus</spn>) of large size and fine
flavor, found in northern Europe and formerly in Scotland; -- called
also <altname>cock of the woods</altname> and <altname>horse of the
wood</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>capercaillie</asp>,
<asp>capercaili</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

